JOHANNESBURG Basic Education minister, Angie Motshekga will visit the families of victims in Friday s tragic accident outside Bronkhorstpruit. Nineteen primary and high school pupils were killed, and seven others injured in the crash.READ: Taxi crash survivor appeals for safe drivingMotshekga will later meet officials from the Gauteng and Mpumalanga provincial government, to discuss funeral arrangements.A committee has already been formed to profile each of the affected families, to determine their immediate needs.Families of those the deceased will identify and verify the bodies of their loved ones on MondayeNCA